Clef.EditorialCommentary: The signature round-b clef in Superius and Tenor - already suggested melodically by passages such as Tenor, mm. 28-9 - is provided explicitly in the canonic resolutions in 1504/3.

Note.EditorialCommentary: Petrucci's resolution departs slightly from the canonic dux here in ornamenting the breve (cf. Contra, m. 32).
beginning of a repeat of mm. 11ff

causes an unprepared essential 4th with the Superius. It is significant in this regard that mm. 37-8 provide the only passage where this voice changes pitch within the breve, or uses a note value smaller than a semibreve; the passage from mm. 35-40 is indeed an ornamented version of mm. 12-17 and 30-5.
